accessibility.info:
Wheelchair & companion seating is available with a 1 to 1 arrangement on three different levels for most events and on the floor when configuration allows. Note: for events where accessible seating is offered on the floor, patrons should be aware that seats are not on a riser so may be obstructed.

Additional companion seats must be purchased in sections nearby so that guests requiring accessible seating on our wheelchair platforms can be accommodated. Depending on show configuration and production requirements, some sections may not be available for all events.

Rogers Arena is fully accessible with a separate dedicateddrop off/pick up entrance (located at Gate 16 on Abbott St.).

Patrons that are picking up tickets at Will Call can arrange with the Guests with Disabilities Office by calling: (604)899-7440, or the Pepsi Live Ticket Centre, to have their tickets held for them at  the WC entrance. (located at Gate 16).

accessibility.info:

The companion seat is located behind the wheelchair patron. If additional companion seats are required, they may be purchased in nearby sections, subject to availability. 

Not all sections will be available for every event.

For some events, there is also Limited Mobility seating in Sections 213-216 and Sections 115-122.for patrons who do not use a wheelchair but need easily accessible seats due to medical or physical reasons.

The accessible drop off & entrance is on the NE corner via Olympic Way above main box office. Parking is on Saddledome grounds via 5th St.

There is an accessible washroom located on the concourse.

No one will be given tickets designated for another person. Proper photo identification is required, and purchasing credit card, if applicable. A signature from the person authorized to pick up the tickets will be obtained at the time of pick up.

venues.parkingDetail: Xcel Energy Center is serviced by two parking ramps (RiverCentre and Kellogg) directly connected to the complex. For most Xcel Energy Center events pre-paid parking is available in the RiverCentre ramp. Please visit the event page of the specific event you are attending to purchase pre-paid parking. - The Saint Paul RiverCentre ramp is situated across from Saint Paul RiverCentre/Xcel Energy Center with the entrance located on the south side of Kellogg Boulevard. - The Kellogg ramp is below Saint Paul RiverCentre with the entrance located on the north side of Kellogg Boulevard. There are numerous other places to park in downtown St. Paul in both covered parking ramps and open lots. Detailed information is available at http://www.xcelenergycenter.com/plan-your-visit/parking.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accommodations include accessible parking and drop-off areas, elevators, escalators, wheelchair accessible seating with excellent sightlines, accessible restrooms. There is elevator access to every level of the arena.

generalInfo.generalRule: Cameras with a detachable lens or lens of more than two (2) inches are prohibited from all Xcel Energy Center concerts. The use of flash photography may also be prohibited. The event producer reserves the right to deny camera use at any time before or during the event and to prohibit the use of any camera that is deemed unacceptable. Video recorders or digital cameras with recording capabilities are prohibited at any time during an event. Xcel Energy Center reserves the right to examine and prohibit use of any camera that staff deem unacceptable. Audio recorders are not allowed at any time. Cans, bottles, coolers and other outside food and beverages are not allowed.
generalInfo.childRule: For most events, including Minnesota Wild games, children under the age of 24 months will be admitted without a ticket if held on an adult's lap. For children's shows such as Disney on Ice, children 12 months and older need a ticket.

We will continue to remain open a minimum of one hour after the start of all paid events and open earlier as needed for early morning/afternoon events or onsales.

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: At the Spring Gateway between the Earth and Sky Casinos Hours: Day of show, will call begins at least 3 hours before the event Monday - Wednesday and noon Thursday - Sunday. Customer must present the actual credit card used for the purchase, a photo ID and Ticketmaster order number in order to receive tickets.

venues.parkingDetail: Numerous garage and lot spaces available. All parking is free. Valet parking also available.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: The Mohegan Sun is an accessible venue for patrons in wheelchairs. They may be purchased at the Box Office, over the phones, or at Ticketmaster retail locations and online.

generalInfo.generalRule: Smoking is only allowed in designated outside areas. No re-entry permitted. Customers will be subject to search and seizure upon arrival. Additional house rules may apply.
generalInfo.childRule: MOHEGAN SUN ARENA EVENTS - Discounts based upon performance / event. All children ages 2 and up must have their own ticket. Children under 12 must be accompanied by an adult. MOHEGAN SUN CABARET EVENTS - No one under 21 allowed unless accompanied by a parent, legal guardian or spouse. MOHEGAN SUN BALLROOM EVENTS- Discounts based upon performance / event. All children ages 2 and up must have their own ticket. Children under 12 must be accompanied by an adult. MOHEGAN SUN WOLF DEN - No under 21 allowed

venues.name: SNHU Arena

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: For general venue information, email info5@snhuarena.com or call (603) 644-5000. For group sales inquiries, email info5@snhuarena.com with the event you are interested in and your message will be directed to the appropriate sales team.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The box office is open day-of-event only for all ticketed events. The box office will open a minimum of 90 minutes prior to the posted event start time. Please check the venue website or social media pages for specific dates and times. The box office is not open for walk-up advance sales on non-event days.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: All major credit cards Visa, MasterCard, Discover and American Express – are accepted at the box office. SNHU Arena is a cashless venue – cash is not accepted as payment at the venue box office or concession stands. No checks of any kind are accepted.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call tickets may be picked up day of show only. No advance pickup of tickets designated as will call delivery will be allowed. Customer must present the credit card used to purchase, a valid matching photo ID, and the Ticketmaster order number in order to claim the tickets.

venues.parkingDetail: There is limited on-site parking available for sale. Passes may be purchased as an add-on either as part of your ticket purchase or through the add-on listings on our Ticketmaster venue page. There are many public and private off-site parking lots within walking distance of the arena. Metered parking is also available on the surrounding streets, please obey posted parking restrictions and time limits. Limited ADA parking is available on-site, accessed off Elm Street via Cedar Street in the southwest corner of the arena property. On-street ADA parking is also available on Chestnut Street at the rear of the arena. ADA spaces are designated for vehicles displaying a current state-issued disability placard or license plate.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: This is an accessible venue, accessible seating is available for purchase via Ticketmaster. To view current available inventory, please visit the Ticketmaster.com purchase page for your desired event.

generalInfo.generalRule: This venue has a clear bag policy: clear totes not exceeding 12"x6"x12" are the only bags permitted. Wristlets are permitted if they do not exceed 4"x6"x1". Backpacks and purses are not permitted. Limited exceptions for medical or diaper bags will be allowed. Camera policy varies by show, please check the venue website or social media for more information. No weapons of any kind. No outside food or beverage. No smoking is allowed and no smoking area is provided.
generalInfo.childRule: Children are welcome. For most events, children under 2 are admitted free if they are seated on a parent or guardians lap. Any children who will be occupying their own seat, regardless of age, must have a ticket. Discounted child tickets may be available for select events, please check the purchase page of your desired event for more information.

events.pleaseNote: Guests attending TD Garden events are advised that laptops, bags, backpacks, luggage, coolers, parcels, briefcases and like articles will be strictly prohibited from the facility. All guests may be subject to search of their person and/or possessions. Patrons with prohibited articles will be turned away and no storage or "check-in area" will be provided. Enforcement will be without exceptions.

generalInfo.generalRule: Alcohol Policy : To purchase alcoholic beverages, a patron must present a valid MA driver's license, MA liquor ID, passport or military ID, which indicates the patron to be a least 21 years of age (MA ID cards, duplicate licenses, expired licenses, damaged licenses and driver's licenses, which do not have photos, will not be accepted). Out of state licenses are acceptable only if the patron is at least 25 years of age and another form of identification (e.g., credit card) will be required if the patron is between 25 and 30 years of age. For out of country patrons, only a valid Passport will be accepted as proof of identification. No smoking is allowed in the building.
generalInfo.childRule: Children under 2 free on adults lap for all events, Celtics, Bruins, family shows, and concerts. Some exceptions may apply.
